Ad [Addendum] Frick: Three Soldiers. There is a comparable group with men in very similar dresses in The Crucifixion, Inv.NÂ° 627, by J.B. in Vienna. A soldier, also seen from the back, in practically the same dress as the drummer, though his-slashed-breeches are a bit broader at the bottom like those a the flute player; to the right of this soldier another, whose dress apart from the last armor is even closer to that of the drummer; he also has an almost identical sword. This second soldier, striding out correspondends to the drummer seen from the front. The drummer's dress also appears in Battle of Arbela (Louvre).
